# ============================================================================
#  WINDOW SNAP CONFIG  —  edit this file to manage your monitors and layouts.
# ============================================================================
#
# This is the EXAMPLE/template. install.sh copies it to
#   ~/.config/yabai/zones.conf
# the first time (and never overwrites it after), because the live file is
# machine-specific and the script appends to it automatically.
#
# There are two kinds of lines (everything else is a comment):
#
#   monitor <uuid> <name> <location>
#       One physical monitor. These are ADDED AUTOMATICALLY the first time the
#       script sees a screen, so this list grows into "every monitor I've ever
#       connected". You edit the <name> and <location> (single words, no spaces).
#       Leave <uuid> alone — it identifies the exact physical screen, even
#       between two identical models or the same model at different offices.
#
#   layout <name> <size> <size> ...
#       The snap zones for the monitor with that <name>: percentages, LEFT->RIGHT,
#       that add up to 100.   e.g.  50 50  |  40 60  |  20 60 20  |  100
#       "layout default ..." is used for any monitor without its own layout line
#       (including freshly auto-added ones, until you give them a name + layout).
#
# To change a size: edit the numbers on a layout line and save. No restart needed.
# Workflow for a new place: plug in monitors, press any shortcut once (this
# registers them at the bottom), then rename them here and add layout lines.
#
# An auto-registered line looks like this (rename it + add a layout):
#   monitor 3FF8CA73-B3D7-439D-A95A-D08584E9B2BA  mon-3FF8CA73  unknown   # 1920pt, first seen 2026-06-15
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Monitors (auto-filled; edit name + location) ---------------------------
#       uuid                                    name      location
monitor 37D8832A-2D66-02CA-B9F7-8F30A301B230  MacBook   laptop     # 1470pt
monitor D587F297-16AB-4B78-A1F2-B04FA6A7A41C  Dell      home       # 2560pt
monitor 269F4E09-0D04-41E9-A7A4-CE591643DAE0  HP        home       # 3440pt

# --- Layouts (sizes per monitor name) ---------------------------------------
layout MacBook  50 50
layout Dell     50 50
layout HP       40 60
layout default  50 50
